caption: We had Brunch this past Sunday with five people. It was our first time at the restaurant. Our experience was very positive. We were seated right away when arriving at the time of our reservation with only two of the five persons in a party ( The others arrived shortly after ) Each one of us got a temperature check. The host and staff were very nice and attentive throughout our entire stay. Ambience was great. Music very nice and the food menu offered a good amount of choices. The food took a little bit longer than usual to come out, but it was nicely presented and everyone enjoyed their dish. Before leaving, we were treated by the owner (manager?) to a mimosa on the house, which was a nice touch. The restaurant has a cool vibe and is a hidden jewel on that block. We would definitely come back and imagine it to be a cool happy hour place as well. Ages in our group were 61, 54, 31, 29 and 23.

It was late on a Wednesday night, my mother and I were on our way back to our hotel. Terravita NYC was the only place we passed that had a nice outdoor seating area that was also heated. You could tell that the owners really spent some money and time making sure that the vestibules outside were comfortable and cozy for the diners. The servers were also super friendly and obviously showed genuine interest in the customers well being.  We ordered the calamari for an appetizer and the braised short rib and chicken panini for our entrees. The 4 stars is because the calamari was tough but had good flavor. My short rib was perfectly cooked and had a nice undertone of rosemary that wasn't overpowering the meat. My mother's chicken panini was crunchy and flavorful made with fresh ingredients.  I ordered the mojito and was pleasantly surprised with a slight effervescence and a punch of fresh mint. I highly recommend the mojito, it was the best I've ever had. My mother's California cabernet was fruity and from a fresh bottle so it wasn't sour.  The drink/spirit menu is extensive and you are sure to find a drink that pleases your taste buds. Overall I recommend this place to anyone but be careful because the bill will rack up. Usually I can't justify spending upwards of $175 on dinner for two with drinks, but this place was definitely worth it!

Decided to check out the restaurant to celebrate my Mom’s birthday. ( It was the highest rated, 4.7, in the area ) Ambiance was beautiful, excellent music and overall vibe. Menu Items Ordered - Drinks: Sangria (Red & White, 3 for $20 during happy hour) and Lemonade (we had a toddler with us) All really good! 😋 Appetizers: Guacamole - good, would have loved the option to make it spicy. Calamari - only thing missing was some sauce. 🙌🏼 Skewers - ended up ordering a 2nd one. Well done comes medium well, still delicious! 😋 Cheeseburger w/ sweet potato fries - my son describes it as ‘very delicious’. 🙌🏼 TerraVita Bowl - Birthday girl loved it! Rich flavor!! Mac n Cheese - (mushrooms can be taken out of platter) Sister says it tasted really good. 😋 Great place to catch up and first dates as music allows for conversation. 🥰 So why did I not give 5 stars? 😓 Confirm end time for happy hour! Website and media pages state 5pm - 8pm Sun. through Thurs. They apparently changed this as of today: 3/4/20. 😒It now ends at 7pm. We got to restaurant after 7pm and ordered drinks at happy hour price. 🤔 Definitely confused... Guess we lucked out at getting first round... 🤷🏻‍♀️ Will follow up with a daytime visit or brunch.

I would say 3.5 stars if I was allowed to give a half star... We checked out this relatively new spot for brunch. The inside was long and narrow and long, clean lines with modern design. They had more seating in the back, the set up can allow larger group comfortably.  The atmosphere was friendly and laid back, but also a bit slow… We ordered Bacon Fritata and Classic Cheese Burger. Fritata was surprisingly good, very fluffy and seasoned just right. It came with something looked like a croquette. Whatever the name of this item is, it was packed with flavor, really delicious!  I add Sunny Side Egg to the Classic Cheese Burger for $1 extra. It came with a side of thick-cut fries and a pickle. The egg was cooked perfectly. The burger didn’t have anything else on it, just the patty, cheese and egg. There was no option to add anything like lettuce or tomato either. Overall, it was a good burger, nice and juicy.  Since they were not huge in portion, we ordered dessert. They didn’t have a dessert menu, but had a couple of desserts to choose from. We chose Chocolate Mousse. It was good, not great, but good.  It was a nice brunch, the service was again very friendly and polite, but can be very slow. It took a while to get a bill, even thought it wasn’t busy in here. Not a place to go if you are in a hurry. The price is a bit high for this neighborhood, especially since the portion is a bit small.

Superb blend of innovative and traditional fare keeps me coming back for old favorites (scrumptious assortment of burgers) and to try some of their more unusual dishes, like lemon ricotta pancakes, layered with fresh cheese and topped with fresh fruit. Check out the menu. I’ve also tried many of their coffees, from expresso and cappuccino to Americano and basic iced—they are rich and have a deep brewed flavor without being bitter or overpowering. Terravita has a cool upscale look (not pretentious) that makes it a great space to hang out, share a meal or have a few drinks. Because it’s open from morning to midnight there’s plenty of opportunity to enjoy the experience. The staff is friendly and attuned to a customer’s preferences.

This was my first time ever trying out a vegan meal  it had a very nice taste  What I thought were French fries were actually deep fried Yuka. I had a nice black bean burger. Not sure how new this place is but I would definitely go back. I highly recommend it for hospitality alone  Great place

Absolutely gorgeous Restaurant, with equally great food and service. As a skeptic I avoided trying the Restaurant but after passing by for several weeks I decided to go in today, and I had a simple Avocado toast with screamed eggs, something I order frequently, and a caffe latte. Boy was it one of the greatest choices I have ever made. I have to tell you if you want an amazing avocado toast this is the place to go! The portion size is great, the price is a little hefty, but I didn't mind paying for it, because it was totally worth it. Definitely will be coming here more often, and I highly reccomend it.

I went for brunch and I agree that this is a healthy place for the neighborhood and there is not that many of those sit down restaurant up here.  But ultimately I didn't fine the brunch menu that interesting and my veggie omlette and home fries where quite bland.  I don't think healthy has to scarifce taste.  The prices are really reasonable and I will come back and try their bowls sometime.  Staff is very friendly.

I have to be honest , I really wanted to love this place but I didn’t . The restaurant is very cute and I enjoyed the ambiance but the food and server didn’t quite meet my expectations. With the prices being high I expected to have quality food but the omelet I ordered on toast was far from that . The toast was stale making it difficult to cut through and the omelet was under seasoned. Furthermore, the server was quite lost and didn’t seem to understand the accommodations I asked for since it’s not what I received . Their was also a delay on him checking up on us or bringing us the check in the end .In addition to this the iced latte I ordered tasted watered down . However the owner was very sweet and attentive.  All in all, seems like it has potential and it’s possible that I didn’t get the best dishes they serve . Would possibly give it another chance in the future.
very warm welcome, everything is very good. I have come twice and I am not disappointed. The  next time i come new York i will come back to this restaurant

Fun breakfast menu with both Dominican elements and other flavors - we got a savory dish of mashed guineito, poached egg, sausage, and cheese as well as a sweeter dish of lemon ricotta pancakes with blueberry compote. All excellent. We also tried the black out smoothie which was delicious and a good price for the amount we got. Overall, very pleased with the experience and thrilled to have another breakfast option in the neighborhood!
We ordered Cobb salad and green chicken pain. Both were excellent. A great addition to the area. Highly recommended.

Amazing place! I have eaten here twice and absolutely love it. The service is outstanding. The, atmosphere is lovely- chill & smooth. Perfect to have a nice dinner or work lunch. Great addition to the neighborhood!!

Fresh, delicious, quality food in a cozy, family friendly, beautiful yet simple environment. Ambience is relaxing and service is sweet and fast. The staff make you feel like you're the most important person in the restaurant. Portions are enough and prices are adequate. 100% recommended

So many photos, but I must be honest in stating it's the best salmon I've had in years.  I order medium well, and it was cooked to perfection...on a bed of rice and sauteed spinach with a punch of great flavors. Totally worth it!

Stephanie and TERRAVITA are EXCEPTIONAL. From the moment we walked into the restaurant, her kind smile and grace lit up the space.  The ambience is cool, fun and hip. The set up gives Washington Heights a flare of midtown, but the music reminds us of the vibrant and wonderful culture around us.  The food: light and refreshing, but bursting with notes of different flavor.  She made sure to get my friend some house made pineapple ketchup and my burrito bowl was not overwhelming. Instead, it cultivated quinoa evenly with pepper and avocado. Allowing all the flavors to pop.  Looking forward to seeing this establishment thrive. Congrats!
